title: Trans Oceanic Magical Cruise
description: It's fun on the high seas as the Titans enjoy a cruise filled with dangerous missions, fast cars, and alien attacks.

title: Creative Geniuses
description: The Titans visit the Jump City Comic Book Con where they meet Marv Wolfman and George Pérez, but also tangle with Control Freak over an exclusive toy.

title: Batman's Birthday Gift
description: The Titans join Robin as he travels to deliver a birthday gift to Batman but they are detoured several times along the way.

title: Polly Ethylene and Tara Phthalate
description: Teen Titans Go takes a comedic look at the superheroes' lives. Viewers finally get the opportunity to watch what life is like for the super teens when their capes are left at home. The teens will deal with everyday issues of adolescence including laundry contests and quests to construct the perfect sandwich.

title: P.P.
description: While stopping a museum theft, the Titans encounter the P.P. Goblin, who uses the Titan's pet peeves against them.

title: TV Knight 3
description: Batman is more interested in watching TV than participating in his birthday party.

title: Carl SanPedro Part 2
description: Carl Sanpedro has struck again, this time in Jamaica, so the Titans take off for the Caribbean.

title: Manor and Mannerisms
description: Robin attends a ball at Wayne Manor hoping to become heir of the mansion, but will the other Titans spoil his chances?

title: Flashback Part 1
description: A flashback reveals how Robin formed the Teen Titans.

title: Doomsday Preppers
description: Teen Titans Go takes a comedic look at the superheroes' lives. Viewers finally get the opportunity to watch what life is like for the super teens when their capes are left at home. The teens will deal with everyday issues of adolescence including laundry contests and quests to construct the perfect sandwich.

title: NBTS 2: Chapter Two
description: In order to stop Ultralak, the Titans must find three music stems, but will need help from a local Miner to get the first stem away from the Sheriff.

title: Kabooms Part 1
description: The Titans are excited to see the movie version of their favorite show "Babies vs Dogs".

title: The Mug
description: Robin dreams of receiving a #1 Dad mug so Raven magically turns them into a sitcom family.

title: Kabooms Part 2
description: Inspired by the "Babies vs Dogs" movie, the Titans decide to make a big Hollywood film of their own.

title: Flashback Part 2
description: A flashback reveals how Robin changed from mild-mannered sidekick to quick-tempered leader.

title: Carl SanPedro Part 1
description: The Titans fly to Los Angeles but end up in San Pedro, where Berto tells them about the villainous long shoreman, Carl Sanpedro.

title: Hafo Safo
description: The Titans travel to the hipster neighborhood of Silver Lake, California to help solve a mystery.

title: Breakfast
description: The Titans discover the joys of eating breakfast food for every meal, but will that lead to an old friend becoming too powerful?

title: Space House Part 3
description: A giant meteor is heading toward the space house, so Starfire, Wonder Woman, Supergirl, and Cyborg takes turns in the holographic chamber to see whose plan will work.

title: NBTS 2: Chapter One
description: The elderly Titans decide to take one last trip to the world of Night Begins to Shine only to encounter a new villian ruling the land, Ultralak.

title: Control Freak
description: When the Titans run amok in the Tower's evidence room, Robin does everything he can to keep things under control.

title: Jam
description: Harley Quinn, Poison Ivy, and Catwoman recruit Starfire and Raven for their roller deby team.

title: Cy & Beasty
description: Cyborg and Beast Boy can't agree on the better character, Tom or Jerry, so they play a little game of cat and mouse.

title: Zimdings
description: When Robin selects the last font on the list for his presentation, it sets off the typocalypse.

title: Marv Wolfman and George Pérez
description: George Perez and Marv Wolfram must pitch an idea for the new Teen Titans in 24 hours, so they brainstorm different concepts for the team.

title: Space House Part 1
description: The Titans set off on an adventure in space, only to find out they'll be sharing their space house with the DC Superhero Girls. The two teams must then discover what goes bump in the night.

title: Pig in a Poke
description: The Titans are worried when Starfire says she has sent all of her money to a prince online, especially when it could be the clown prince himself.

title: How's This for a Special? Spaaaace Part 1
description: After receiving a galactic crime alert, the Titans take off for an epic space adventure.

title: Space House Part 2
description: After Beast Boy steals the power ring and jumps into Zatanna's hat, Green Lantern must deal with being powerless as she and her friends give chase.

title: T is for Titans
description: The Titans are shocked to learn that the T Tower had previous owners.

title: A Little Help Please
description: When they receive a distress call from the TTG animators and artists, the Titans must tone down their actions and avoid big adventures.

title: TV Knight 6
description: Batman is forced to go to the department store with Alfred, but runs off to watch TV with Commissioner Gordon.

title: Fat Cats
description: Teen Titans Go takes a comedic look at the superheroes' lives. Viewers finally get the opportunity to watch what life is like for the super teens when their capes are left at home. The teens will deal with everyday issues of adolescence including laundry contests and quests to construct the perfect sandwich.

title: EEBows
description: Tired of getting pinched, the Titans' elbows rebel and soon bend the very fabric of time and space.

title: DC
description: It's Wonder Woman's 80th birthday, so the Titans head to DC Headquarters for the party.

title: Space House Part 4
description: The free vacation in space was just an elaborate plot by Brainiac to collect every hero and villain in the DC Multiverse. The Titans and Superhero Girls agree to help Brainiac become an adult in exchange for letting them go.

title: A Holiday Story
description: Santa Claus enlists Beast Boy's help in getting him back into the Holiday Mob, which is run by Baby New Year.

title: How's This for a Special? Spaaaace Part 2
description: The Titans have to stop Darkseid's latest scheme, but the excitement of the space adventure might be too much for Robin to handle.

title: What a Boy Wonders
description: Robin forms a book club to debut his new autobiography, but the Titans would rather discuss other books.

title: Captain Cool
description: The Titans' antics with their imaginary friend Captain Cool annoy Robin until make-believe starts becoming real.

title: TV Knight 5
description: Batman pretends to be sick to avoid work so he and Commissioner Gordon can run around town watching their favorite shows.

title: Pepo The Pumpkinman
description: A magic hat brings the Titans' pumpkinman to life, but they have to figure out how to keep Pepo from rotting.
